techniques, the layout in the kitchen,

856
01:14:30,926 --> 01:14:33,087
even the lacquering process
for all the timber.

857
01:14:33,262 --> 01:14:36,675
It's something Kim and I are very
proud of, and I'm sure all of you,

858
01:14:36,849 --> 01:14:39,261
with your vast
array of expertise,

859
01:14:39,393 --> 01:14:41,850
will appreciate
the attention to detail.

860
01:14:43,105 --> 01:14:45,562
The art you see on
the walls, the friezes,

861
01:14:45,649 --> 01:14:48,686
even the furniture
that you're sitting on,

862
01:14:48,861 --> 01:14:52,774
has all been meticulously
chosen, reassembled or restored,

863
01:14:52,865 --> 01:14:54,901
depending on
its condition,

864
01:14:55,075 --> 01:14:59,193
to, I think, truly represent the
essence of the Blackwood collection.

865
01:14:59,371 --> 01:15:01,236
So, thank you to
the heritage board

866
01:15:01,415 --> 01:15:04,657
for their assistance, and
to the historical society,

867
01:15:07,296 --> 01:15:10,129
and, of course, to our guest
of honor, Charles Jacoby.

868
01:15:11,175 --> 01:15:13,666
Your interest
in our projects

869
01:15:13,802 --> 01:15:16,339
is nothing short of
inspirationa! So, thank you.

870
01:15:17,014 --> 01:15:19,676
And finally,
to the house itself.

871
01:15:19,850 --> 01:15:22,842
May its newly restored
life be long and happy.

